This file describes features that are not yet implemented, and bugs that are
not yet fixed. Items are grouped by priority for production readiness.

=== Known bugs ===

* (bug) net/inbound: crates can listen on any ports for inbound connections,
  but connections are rejected from the host itself.
  See bug#239590: ipfw rule doesn't forward TCP connections made through
  the host's LAN address.

=== High priority — blocking production use ===

(High-priority items above are now complete; the next batch is
operational quality.)

=== Medium priority — operational quality ===

* (feature) crate top — live resource monitor across all running
  containers (like htop).

* (feature) Auto-create bridge — if the specified bridge interface does
  not exist, create it automatically (opt-in via
  auto_create_bridge: true in crate.yml).

* (feature) crated F2 write API — the daemon currently only has read-only
  endpoints. Need POST/DELETE for container lifecycle, WebSocket console,
  stats streaming, snapshot and export/import management.

=== Low priority — future enhancements ===

* (feature) SNMP AgentX: the AgentX wire protocol is not yet implemented
  (snmpd runs in stub mode).

* (feature) Hub web dashboard — hub/web/ directory is empty. Need minimal
  HTML/JS UI: node list, container list by node, CPU/RAM metrics,
  start/stop controls (requires F2 API).

* (feature) Inter-container DNS — built-in DNS service for .crate zone
  so containers can resolve each other by name without manual /etc/hosts.

* (feature) WireGuard/IPsec tunnels — VPN support between hosts for
  multi-host container networking.

* (feature) Rootless containers — crate is setuid root (04755). Explore
  rootless jail via jail(8) with allow.nfds.

* (feature) Container migration — automated export → transfer → import
  between hosts via crate-hub.

* (feature) Hub scheduling — automatic container placement on the least
  loaded host.

* (feature) Layered images — ZFS-based layering through clones instead
  of monolithic .crate archives.

* (feature) crate update TARGET — in-place base system and package update
  inside a running jail without full recreate.

* (feature) Man pages for crated(8) and crate-hub(8).

* (feature) crate inspect TARGET — full JSON dump of running container
  configuration (spec, runtime, network, mounts).

=== Done (removed) ===

Items completed and removed from this file:
- Configuration management (0.2.0 — lib/config.cpp, 3-tier system)
- Health checks (0.2.3 — healthcheck: spec section)
- Container dependencies (0.2.3 — depends: spec section)
- crate stack multi-container orchestration (0.2.3)
- Enhanced crate list with ports/mounts/healthcheck columns (0.2.3)
- CHANGELOG.md (0.2.0)
- Native FreeBSD API wrappers replacing shell commands (0.2.5)
- crate stop TARGET (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- crate restart TARGET (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- crate stats TARGET with JSON support (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- crate logs TARGET with follow/tail (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- Restart policy (on-failure/always/unless-stopped) with retry loop (0.3.15)
- Graceful shutdown with configurable timeout (0.3.0 — lifecycle.cpp)
- Per-container firewall policy with IPv4+IPv6 (0.3.0 — PfctlOps)
- Per-stack DNS via unbound (0.3.0 — stack.cpp)
- Inter-container network policies (0.3.0 — stack.cpp)
- IP pool allocator for stacks (0.3.0 — stack.cpp)
- RCTL I/O enforcement with verification (0.3.0 — run_jail.cpp)
- OOM detection and exit diagnostics (0.3.0 — run_jail.cpp)
- Per-container Prometheus metrics (0.3.0 — daemon/metrics.cpp)
- ZFS disk quotas per-container (0.3.0 — zfs_ops.cpp)
- Base system caching with SHA256 (0.3.0 — create.cpp)
- CI: Linux unit tests, FreeBSD lite/full build, release binary workflow
- pkg/add support — install pre-built .txz files via `pkg add` (0.5.5)
- X11 shared-mode security warning at validate + run time (0.5.6)
- pkg/chroot output captured to /var/log/crate/create-<jail>.log (0.5.7)
- Symmetric encryption for .crate (AES-256-CBC + PBKDF2 via -P) (0.5.4)
- ed25519 signing for .crate (-K to sign, -V to verify; .sig sidecar) (0.5.8)
- Audit logging — JSONL append to /var/log/crate/audit.log (0.5.9)
- Cross-device file shares — single-file nullfs bind fallback when host
  and jail-side path are on different devices (0.6.0 — lib/share_pure.cpp)
